#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Natumhākavagga "
msgstr "4. It’s Not Yours "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 35. Aññatarabhikkhusutta → paṭhamabhikkhusuttaṃ (bj) | bhikkhu 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Aññatarabhikkhusutta "
msgstr "35. A Mendicant "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.35, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.35:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.35:1.3"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu; "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” "

msgctxt "sn22.35:1.4"
msgid "yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho, appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:1.5"
msgid "“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, anuseti, tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "“Mendicant, you’re defined by what you have an underlying tendency for. "

msgctxt "sn22.35:1.6"
msgid "yaṃ nānuseti, na tena saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "You’re not defined by what you have no underlying tendency for.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:1.7"
msgid "“Aññātaṃ, bhagavā, aññātaṃ, sugatā”ti. "
msgstr "“Understood, Blessed One! Understood, Holy One!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.35:2.1"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsī”ti? "
msgstr "“But how do you see the detailed meaning of my brief statement?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:2.2"
msgid "“Rūpañce, bhante, anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“If you have an underlying tendency for form, you’re defined by that. "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.3"
msgid "Vedanañce anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "If you have an underlying tendency for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.4"
msgid "Saññañce anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.5"
msgid "Saṅkhāre ce anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.6"
msgid "Viññāṇañce anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "consciousness, you’re defined by that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:2.7"
msgid "Rūpañce, bhante, nānuseti na tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "If you have no underlying tendency for form, you’re not defined by that. "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.8"
msgid "Vedanañce … "
msgstr "If you have no underlying tendency for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.9"
msgid "saññañce … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.10"
msgid "saṅkhāre ce … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:2.11"
msgid "viññāṇañce nānuseti na tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "consciousness, you’re not defined by that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:2.12"
msgid "Imassa khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.35:3.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu. "
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicant! "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsi. "
msgstr "It’s good that you understand the detailed meaning of what I’ve said in brief like this. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:3.3"
msgid "Rūpañce, bhikkhu, anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "If you have an underlying tendency for form, you’re defined by that. "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.4"
msgid "Vedanañce … "
msgstr "If you have an underlying tendency for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.5"
msgid "saññañce … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre ce … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.7"
msgid "viññāṇañce anuseti tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "consciousness, you’re defined by that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:3.8"
msgid "Rūpañce, bhikkhu, nānuseti na tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "If you have no underlying tendency for form, you’re not defined by that. "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.9"
msgid "Vedanañce … "
msgstr "If you have no underlying tendency for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.10"
msgid "saññañce … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.11"
msgid "saṅkhāre ce … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.35:3.12"
msgid "viññāṇañce nānuseti na tena saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "consciousness, you’re not defined by that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:3.13"
msgid "Imassa kho, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena, bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena attho daṭṭhabbo”ti. "
msgstr "This is how to understand the detailed meaning of what I said in brief.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.36, sc4
msgctxt "sn22.35:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "And then that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.35:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Then that mendicant, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.35:5.2"
msgid "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "sn22.35:5.3"
msgid "Aññataro ca pana so bhikkhu arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And that mendicant became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.35:5.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

